parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front strut can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Abnormal noise
clunking noise
smoke coming from the front of the vehicle
vehicle dropping to the ground
steering wheel vibration
inability to control the vehicle
tire damage
and damage to other components.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to honor recall repairs can lead to continued safety risks and potential accidents.
symptoms: Denial of recall repairs
refusal to reimburse for independent repairs
and lack of assistance from the manufacturer.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the emergency brake can lead to a loss of vehicle control, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The emergency brake does not operate normally
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the vehicle is unable to stop properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cooling system can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine damage, stalling, or even engine failure, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle is running hot
the temperature gauge is in the red zone
the coolant level is low
the vehicle is overheating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature brake rotor wear can lead to reduced braking performance, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake rotors wear out prematurely
the brakes are screeching or squeaking
the vehicle is vibrating when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission's reverse function can cause the vehicle to be unable to shift into reverse gear, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to engage in reverse gear
the transmission slips from gear to gear
the gear position indicator shows incorrect gear selection
the vehicle jerks or accelerates randomly.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Defective Light Control Module (LCM) Causing Headlight Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The defective LCM can cause the headlight to stay on even after the vehicle is turned off, leading to a fire hazard.
symptoms: The headlight stays on after the vehicle is turned off
the headlight catches fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Malfunction Due to Water Ingress
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water ingress into the transmission's wiring and switch can cause electrical malfunction, leading to incorrect gear selection and indication, and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The transmission slips from gear to gear
the gear position indicator shows incorrect gear selection
the vehicle jerks or accelerates randomly.
